      "id": "5d17a2ca_9a7d9605",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/run-all-tests.sh",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 31,
      "message": "Solution doesn't work and still produces gigabytes of logs.\n\nI think issue here is that the error.log is not in this directory. Also, it can't rotate anything: since this script runs as a pipeline job, we are checking out a fresh repo each run. So the log rotation is just 'rotating' a single log file. Really this solution a very complicated way of compressing a single log file.\n\nI recommend just redirecting all errors to /dev/null, and revisit other solutions later if we need logging.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
